.TH GLIIM 2gg $VERSION $DATE Development Tools
.SH NAME
purge-index \-  (index)
.SH PURPOSE
Delete all index nodes.

.SH SYNTAX

.RS 4
.EX

purge-index <index> 

.EE
.RE

.SH DESCRIPTION
purge-index will delete all <index> nodes; <index> must have been created with \fBnew-index\fP. All of <index>'s nodes, and their keys/values all deleted.

After purge-index, the index is empty and you can use it again (write into it, read from it etc.).

.SH EXAMPLES
Delete all index data:

.RS 4
.EX

new-index myindex
\[char46]..
purge-index myindex 

.EE
.RE

